# Graphify (optional)

This repo has an optional [graphify](https://github.com/Graphify-Labs/graphify) knowledge graph for `app/` at `graphify-out/` (repo root, not under `app/`). Prefer Cursor’s normal Read / Grep / Glob when those are enough. Use graphify when a cross-file map, god-node view, or symbol-to-symbol path would help — it is not required before exploring code.

## When it may help

- “What connects X to Y?” / dependency path between symbols
- Broad architecture orientation (hubs, communities) without reading many files
- Checking whether a change sits near a high-degree hub (`RunControlService`, `ControlPlaneService`, etc.)

## Commands

Graph root: `graphify-out/graph.json` (from repo root).

```bash
graphify query "<question>" --graph graphify-out/graph.json
graphify path "<A>" "<B>" --graph graphify-out/graph.json
graphify explain "<concept>" --graph graphify-out/graph.json
```

- `graphify-out/graph.html` — interactive browser view
- `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` — god nodes, communities, suggested questions
- After substantial `app/` edits, optionally refresh with `graphify extract ./app --out . --code-only` (AST-only, no API cost)
